reviews.text: Awesome place. Service is real good. Food tastes good. Friendly staff. Drinks available. They have daily offers on drinks. Make sure to check out the outside boards for offers.
Wine on the menu not available! Really shocking. Incomprehensible for a luxury hotel. Service below par.
Their afternoon brunch on Sundays is a feast fit for royals - everything is always perfect!
Wonderful ambiance , really sublime fine dining experience
nice place

I remember seeing the name and thinking "maybe this is some discount place or all you can eat buffet".  I was wrong!  This place is nice inside with a wonderful atmosphere.  Fish is fresh, tasty, and their service is excellent.  I have yet to have a bad night there.  Average prices for sushi, but the quality is well worth the price you pay.

Has great service. Servers are very attentive and friendly. Food was good and satisfying. I'd would had given a 5 stars if it wasnt for-
1. I feel that the portion of the food for its price... was a bit too small. $9 for combo fried rice, I could had gotten a bigger portion else where for that price. 
2. Our sushi kept falling apart, all of them. Maybe it was just that particular day or the chef working but none stayed intact. 

Overall, it's a good establishment. No complaints other than size of entree (not sushi).

We have eaten at Mr. Sushi for many years. The price is very fair compared to other sushi shops, but the service and quality beats everyone else. We've tried a lot of places over the years and always end up comparing them to Mr. Sushi. I love the more traditional atmosphere and attire. I also enjoy the serenade when there's a birthday. So fun! I also appreciate that most of the staff has been the for many years. It's so nice to see the same smiling, gracious faces when you walk in. Our favorites are the Addison tower, volcano rolls, eel sushi, baby scallops, albacore, fresh salmon, and Mr. Sushi rolls.
Most authentic and delicious Japanese food in town. Great date night spot. Fast and polite service in a beautiful atmosphere. Try the Mr. Sushi Roll!

There are many sushi places like Mr. Sushi but this is My Sushi place! I particularly love practicing my Japanese with my Chef's. I adore it when they give me a hard time and tell me they are all out of salmon skin and I make them laugh when I act surprised when my salmon skin roll appears in front of me magically. :-) This is My Sushi place...

I'd have to give more than five stars just for the service. The owner and her daughter were extraordinarily accommodating. I had a hard time enjoying their version of pad Thai. I'm not sure if it's me or the food itself. However, the kitchen and server more than made up for it. i ate their curry instead. The rest of the food was great.

Awesome Thai food each individual dish cook to customers preferences. All the dishes have its own unique taste and flavor. I highly recommend you try all of their dishes if possible.The atmosphere and setting will take your breath away .Original family own since it first open in the early 1990's and still running strong.

Both superlative and lousy, one experience of each in our two visits from afar.  Summer-- lobster stew special was supreme, generous, great side dishes left us eager to return.   Winter-- seafood soup inedibly  salty and not flavorful but generous seafood content.  Pad Thai bizarre with possible bottled sauce? No texture and repellent taste- not a dish anyone had ever messed up in our history.  Promised vegetable addition was missing from dishes.  Has ownership changed?

What was once a reliable restaurant has now become a half hazard excuse for a business, much less eaterie. The hours of operation are sporadic,  closing down for periodic emergencies. When we ordered take out we were told to arrive at a specific time. We drove in late to give them extra time, but when we arrived we were told that our order would be a half hour or more, and the poor waitress looked stressed out. There was no one in the restaurant but one poor guy who was told the same thing and ordered another beer. In short, the place looks more like a pathetic storefront for a nature photographer and jewelry maker than a bonafide restaurant. It is a ghost of its former self. Time to give up the ghost. Terrible excuse for a restaurant 
.

Stood in lobby/reception/photography studio/eBay store waiting to be seated until we got sick of that. Went to the bar to ask if we were waiting in the right place and was greeted by a miserable slob that hated her job. She then told us that the table that was practically in the vestibule was "all she had" even though the actual restaurant of this multiuse building was unavailable. We left (and I told her) because "she sucks".
If this THING is an owner that's sad, if not should be fired.

I've been here three times. Looks clean and pretty good service, no problems finding a parking spot. The food is good and I would give more stars if they would get my order right. I ordered three orders of veggie rice without egg. Every time at least one of the orders has had egg and even once got egg and chicken. After the second time my SO complained that his rice was crunchy.

Did this place get new owners?  Cash only with an atm in the entryway. (3$ for those who don't carry cash).  We ordered lunch here and the vegetable curry was kind of cold. The rest if the food was cool too. A little heavy on the red pepper so watch the spice level. The food just wasn't the same. Haven't been here in about a year but, it wasn't the same.  Service was ok. Lunch for 2 with soup and an app was 36.00.
Best place to get Thai food..... If you love spicy food come here.... They also have other selection of you don't like spicy food
Food very ordinary.  I love Thai food but this one is near the bottom.  I went with a friend.  Both of our meals were slightly hotter than room temperature.  Pretty boring.  Not recommended.
must be under new ownership. seems the quality of food has changed as well as they are now cash only? not a fan

I love this place we ordered their spring rolls definitely get the full appetizer. One is not enough. I could have eaten all eight by myself. They were definitely house made. Our waitress Sue actually helps make them. The staff spends hours making them. They fry them to order. My entree was amazing next time I'll get it at 3 stars of heat. My date got a curry dish and I liked it more than my noodle dish. For kids I would suggest the chicken appetizer with some rice and more spring rolls. The wait staff was amazing. Definitely will be going back and sending all of my friends and family.

It's located in the cozy popular 5 Points neighborhood which means parking is a bit limited. I ordered a cashew nut stirfry which was quite flavorful and Thai hot as I had hoped. 😊However, I ordered tofu as my protein with extra broccoli and the portions were disappointingly small even for a lunch menu. But I'm game to go again and check out the dinner menu and evening ambiance.
Delicious food, friendly and helpful service, great prices. The soups were excellent. I had spicy fried rice and thoroughly enjoyed it.
I've been going there since 1999. Same menu, same flavor, same location. Great place to try traditional Thai cuisine.

Ordered 2 pots of coconut soup, one w tofu and one w extra shrimp. The soup wasntwgood. It didn't have coconut taste. Tofu was tough, almost hard .The one w shrimp, had 6 med ones, also looks like broth from beef not coconut at all .Spri Sp rolls are smaller than before and hollow. Big waste of money. Since they changed hands, I guess they changed recipes. I don't like the change.
Quiet place, very friendly staff and a broad enough menu to keep everyone guessing what they want. Lunch specials are around $10 with most entrees around $14. Great place for a quick bite.

Everyone here was so extremly nice to me and they all were stop helpful! (I've never eaten Thai before) The food was great, the drink was great & the service was just awesome! I wish all places were as friendly as they were here!

Came in today. Waited 45 mins thinking the food is almost ready. When I go and ask the worker about the wait time for food, she says it will take another 10 mins. Canceled the order and left with no food. Who takes 50+ mins to cook during lunch hour. Plus it was only one person serving all the customers and it took some time before she came to take our order. If you know it's going to be busy, have more people to help during peak hours. This is unacceptable. I would not give a star but that's the only option available. I would not recommend this place.

You couldn't ask for a better Panda the green beans and chicken was better than I've had anywhere it was super unlike the one that's over by the Vallarta store on Clinton and Weber this one here gets an A+ and that one over there gets an F don't bother to go there cuz their food is terrible. Also the help over here on Shaw is much more friendly and it's an all-around better experience
Place is decorated really nice for the holidays and food/service is good. Karaoke in the summer....

I ordered fresh vegetable egg rolls and a tofu veg curry dish with a side of white rice. 
The egg rolls were very good despite the sauce being more soy than peanuts.  The curry dish was all kinds  of wrong.  It was gloppy and bland with the merest hint of curry. I wish the chef had come out to say sorry we're out of curry today please order something else. Perhaps we should have gotten Pho everyone seemed to be enjoying that

As a Dorchester local, I’ve been coming here for years and will probably keep coming. The food is delicious and pretty authentic. That being said, I cannot stress enough how this establishment needs to better train its staff. Every time I come, we never get checked on or simple parts of our meal are forgotten. The worst part is having to wait so long to pay the check. I always want to recommend this place to friends but until I know they will have a good experience, I’m sometimes hesitate. Overall, I’m hoping this note will improve the wait staff training and attentiveness.
I think what sets Pho Hoa apart from other similar places in the area is the atmosphere. They've put effort into making it classy and cozy, and it shows. The food, of course, is fantastic.

This pho is fantastic and affordable. The atmosphere is inviting and cozy while also being decorative. They play some great Vietnamese hip-hop inspired pop. 

Come here for a date night on a budget 😉.
Been eating here for over 20 yrs. Hopefully, another 20. When you think pho, Pho Hoa will not disappoint, not ever. Always pleasant staff, too.

My sister for a cake from here and my boyfriend went to go pick it up. When he got there it took 10 minutes for a subway employee to help him out because there weren't any maggie moo employees there. Once he got the cake it looked horrific, it looked like a child wrote on it. My sister wanted to talk to a manager there was none, needless to say my sister had him return it so they could go to another maggie moo location. Maggie moo is our favorite ice cream stop and it is so disappointing that this happened. If you can't manage a location, close it down or you will just build bad rapport.
